http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: This course focuses on environmental concerns related to soil, air, and water. Emphasis is placed on soil and water in relation to agricultural processes. Students also will investigate ways to prevent contamination and conserve soil and water.
Environmental Concerns
Define terms
Match terms with definitions
Identify areas of environmental concern
Research each area of environmental concern (soil, water, wildlife, air, climate, wetlands, and waste management)
Discuss career opportunities relating to environmental science
Research a career in environmental resource management to determine educational requirements, working conditions, and salary
Identify FFA activities that support an interest in soil and water management
Participate in FFA activities related to environmental resources.

Match terms to their definitions

Have students name examples of accidents that have occurred locally in environmental resources work

Work together with others to promote safety in environmental resources
Take a test on environmental resources safety before beginning work
